# Import necessary libraries for data visualization
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Create subplots for both Maths and Portuguese datasets

axes[0, 0].set_xlabel('Workday Alcohol Consumption (Dalc)')
axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Final Grade (G3)')

axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('Final Grade (G3)')

# Plot for Portuguese dataset
sns.scatterplot(data=portuguese_df, x='Dalc', y='G3', hue='sex', ax=axes[1, 0])
axes[1, 0].set_title('Portuguese: Workday Alcohol Consumption vs Final Grade')
axes[1, 0].set_xlabel('Workday Alcohol Consumption (Dalc)')
axes[1, 0].set_ylabel('Final Grade (G3)')

axes[1, 1].set_title('Portuguese: Weekend Alcohol Consumption vs Final Grade')
axes[1, 1].set_xlabel('Weekend Alcohol Consumption (Walc)')
axes[1, 1].set_ylabel('Final Grade (G3)')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Import the required libraries for Excel file formatting
import openpyxl
from openpyxl.styles import Font, Alignment, Border, Side, PatternFill

# Create a new Excel workbook and add sheets
wb = openpyxl.Workbook()
overview_sheet = wb.active
overview_sheet.title = "Overview"
analysis_sheet = wb.create_sheet("Analysis")
conclusion_sheet = wb.create_sheet("Conclusions")

# Function to apply basic cell formatting
def format_cell(cell, font_size=11, bold=False, border_style=None, fill=None):
    cell.font = Font(size=font_size, bold=bold)
    cell.alignment = Alignment(horizontal='left', vertical='center')
    if border_style:
        cell.border = Border(left=Side(style=border_style),
                             right=Side(style=border_style),
                             top=Side(style=border_style),
                             bottom=Side(style=border_style))
    if fill:
        cell.fill = PatternFill(start_color=fill, end_color=fill, fill_type="solid")

# Add content to Overview sheet
overview_sheet['A1'] = "Student Performance Analysis Report"
format_cell(overview_sheet['A1'], font_size=14, bold=True)

# Add dataset description
overview_sheet['A3'] = "Dataset Description:"
format_cell(overview_sheet['A3'], font_size=12, bold=True)
overview_content = (
    "The dataset used in this analysis includes student performance in secondary education "
    "of two Portuguese schools. It contains various attributes including student grades, demographic, "
    "social, and school-related features. The dataset provides performance data for two subjects: "
    "Mathematics (mat) and Portuguese language (por)."
)
overview_sheet['A4'] = overview_content
overview_sheet['A4'].alignment = Alignment(wrap_text=True)
overview_sheet.column_dimensions['A'].width = 100

# Add analysis intention
overview_sheet['A6'] = "Analysis Intention:"
format_cell(overview_sheet['A6'], font_size=12, bold=True)
overview_sheet['A7'] = (
    "The primary goal of this analysis is to understand the factors affecting student performance "
    "in Mathematics and Portuguese. Various visual and statistical methods have been used to "
    "identify relationships between student grades and other attributes."
)
overview_sheet['A7'].alignment = Alignment(wrap_text=True)

# Populate Analysis sheet with visual analysis conclusions
analysis_sheet['A1'] = "Visual Analysis Summary"
format_cell(analysis_sheet['A1'], font_size=14, bold=True)

# Math Analysis
analysis_sheet['A3'] = "Mathematics:"
format_cell(analysis_sheet['A3'], font_size=12, bold=True)
math_analysis_content = (
    "1. Alcohol Consumption: Higher alcohol consumption is generally associated with lower grades.\n"
    "2. Travel Time: Longer travel times to school are associated with lower grades.\n"
    "3. Age: Older students tend to have lower grades."
)
analysis_sheet['A4'] = math_analysis_content
analysis_sheet['A4'].alignment = Alignment(wrap_text=True)

# Portuguese Analysis
analysis_sheet['A6'] = "Portuguese:"
format_cell(analysis_sheet['A6'], font_size=12, bold=True)
portuguese_analysis_content = (
    "1. Alcohol Consumption: Higher alcohol consumption is generally associated with lower grades.\n"
    "2. Travel Time: Longer travel times to school do not show a strong relationship with grades.\n"
    "3. Age: Older age is not strongly correlated with grades."
)
analysis_sheet['A7'] = portuguese_analysis_content
analysis_sheet['A7'].alignment = Alignment(wrap_text=True)

# Populate Conclusion sheet
conclusion_df.to_excel(conclusion_sheet, index=False, startrow=1)
for row in conclusion_sheet.iter_rows(min_row=2, max_row=conclusion_df.shape[0]+1, min_col=1, max_col=3):
    for cell in row:
        format_cell(cell, border_style='thin')

# Add title to the Conclusion sheet
conclusion_sheet['A1'] = "Factors Affecting Academic Performance"
format_cell(conclusion_sheet['A1'], font_size=14, bold=True)

# Save the workbook
excel_report_path = '/mnt/data/Student_Performance_Comprehensive_Report.xlsx'
wb.save(excel_report_path)

excel_report_path
